In case you missed it, here are the top News stories of the week: 1. Cyril's millions: GTI and Ford Ranger seized The cars bought with money stolen from President Cyril Ramaphosa's farm were reportedly seized by the Namibian authorities. 2. 'I married a MERMAID for power, riches and fame!' Self-confessed former occultist Jay Isreal Senior said he was once given the option to sleep with a dead woman for power, fame and fortune. 3. Zion Christian Church robbers bust! Daring robbers got into the Zion Christian Church headquarters in Moria, Polowane in April and made off with with the money from the collection box. 4. Shock after soccer star found dead! Residents of Rolle outside Thulamahashe near Bushbuckridge Mpumalanga were shocked when they discovered the body of rising soccer star Nhlamulo "Spikiri" Mathebula. 5. Kagiso fights load shedding with his own invention From a young age, Kagiso Domingos has been obsessed with figuring out how things worked and how to make them better.